^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|They have a known 8 card fit at least, and good chance Anna has six clubs and  3C is the bid. Elizabeth was lucky to go down only one, if spades were split differently, down two at least. Now, back to Kia. By the law of total tricks, and my competitive guidelines, Kia should bid 3C. Remember, if they have a fit and you have a fit, you should always bid to the 3 level if they are at the 2 level. And you should bid 3 over 3 if you  have a 9 card fit or a singleton in their suit. Those are good guidelines to remember, easy and very effective.|
